The course introduces the vocabulary related to the following topics: past events, describing people; proposals, advices and assumptions; travelling; asking for information; expressing an opinion. Grammar: imperfetto and passato prossimo; use of condizionale; pronomi diretti + participio passato; use of imperativo.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The cours aims at systematic development of all four language skills (reading, writing, listening, speaking) through a wide variety of tasks.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course the students will be able to:  - understand and compose different texts in Italian;  - use the vocabulary and grammar covered during the course in everyday situations;  - have a conversation and understand a spoken text both in present and past.
